  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The prognosis of chronic hepatitis C virus (HCV)infeciton varies from minimal progressive
      disease to cirrhosis or hepatocellular carcinoma. Host genetic factors contribute to disease
      severity. It is known that cytokine gene (including tumor necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-alpha)
      and interleukin-10 (IL-10) polymorphism affect disease prognosis.This study aims to assess
      the effect of TNF-alpha and IL-10, and their interaction,on prognosis of HCV-related chronic
      liver disease
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
